Author: Abe Kabakoff <occamsshavingkit@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Jun 19 06:37:36 2026 +0000

    fix(010 US1): bound Argument value_rank — fix fuzz-found 8.45 GB allocation DoS (SC-001)
    
    The T014 fuzz pass found a real remote-reachable allocation DoS: Argument::decode
    did `array_dimensions.resize(value_rank as usize, 0)` with an attacker-controlled
    i32 value_rank. A 30-byte message with value_rank ≈ 2.1e9 drove an 8.45 GB
    allocation (malloc(8455716864)).
    
    Bound value_rank by max_array_length (default 1000) before the resize → clean
    decode error on absurd values; sane value_ranks unchanged. Regression test decodes
    the exact crafted artifact and asserts an error (not OOM); valid value_rank=2 still
    pads correctly. Post-fix fuzz_deserialize: 45s / 3M runs, peak RSS ~436 MB (was
    8.45 GB), no OOM/crash. All 3 fuzz targets now clean → SC-001 met.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

